## Constraints

### MUST:
- Define every external dependency as an outbound port owned by the core
- Wire adapters to ports at composition root
- Keep the core compilable and testable without any adapter present
- Apply contract tests to every adapter implementing an outbound port
- {{MUST_RULES}}

### MUST NOT:
- Import adapter packages from core code
- Leak adapter-specific types (e.g. `*sql.Rows`, `*http.Request`) across port boundaries
- Couple the core to a specific framework, DB driver, or message broker
- Skip the port and call adapters directly from core
- {{MUST_NOT_RULES}}

